hopobject.body: Who do you work for? fenelon falls pharmacy hours But Richard Jeffrey, of fund manager Cazenove, said debts being amassed now could create a rerun of the crisis. He said: "The reason the UK recession was so deep was that the household sector had previously got itself into dire financial straits – encouraged, it may be added, by a protracted period of below-normal interest rates. Debt-to-income levels rose to unprecedented highs, leaving borrowers massively squeezed when interest rates rose and again when real incomes were squeezed by persistently high inflation."
